neers%20working%20in%20or%20planning%20to%20work%20in%20Wall%20Street's%20tech%20ranks%20is%20to%20embrace%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20environment%20is%20constantly%20changing.%20This%20is%20especially%20true%20because%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20industry%20is%20ripe%20for%20AI%20disruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20much%20of%20the%20business%20is%20digitized%2C%20but%20the%20complexities%20of%20the%20business%20(from%20developing%20software%20for%20different%20financial%20instruments%20to%20the%20regulatory%20nuances%20of%20emerging%20markets)%20has%20largely%20held%20the%20industry%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20engineers%20interested%20in%20applying%20technology%20to%20solve%20interesting%20problems%2C%20and%20particularly%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20the%20AI%20disruption%20will%20occur%2C%20I%20think%20this%20actually%20would%20be%20an%20industry%20to%20watch%2C%26quot%3B%20Gaysinskiy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpoint72-cto-ilya-gaysinskiy-tech-talent-ai-plans-hedge-fund-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743584822000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ec0320b8b41a9673fc45d2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpoint72-cto-ilya-gaysinskiy-tech-talent-ai-plans-hedge-fund-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20his%20first%20interview%2C%20Ilya%20Gaysinskiy%20outlines%20his%20tech%20ambitions%20for%20Point72%2C%20from%20AI%20to%20global%20expansion%20and%20culture.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bschan%40businessinsider.com%20(Bianca%20Chan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpoint72-cto-ilya-gaysinskiy-tech-talent-ai-plans-hedge-fund-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I've%20negotiated%20up%20to%20%2430%2C000%20more%20than%20I%20was%20offered%20in%20each%20new%20job%20using%20the%20'door-in-the-face'%20technique.%20Here's%20how%20it%20works.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20businessman%20with%20a%20speech%20bubble%20and%20money%20emojis.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67dae4f6585f1dff88b295b7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Chelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETJ%20Patel%20uses%20the%20'door-in-the-face'%20technique%20to%20negotiate%20higher%20salaries%20in%20software%20engineering.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20strategy%20involves%20making%20a%20high%20initial%20request%20and%20then%20a%20more%20reasonable%20follow-up.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPatel%20secured%20offers%20%2410%2C000%20to%20%2430%2C000%20above%20initial%20proposals%20using%20this%20method.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20TJ%20Patel%2C%20a%2027-year-old%20software%20engineer%20in%20Austin%20who%20asked%20that%20BI%20not%20name%20his%20employers.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20Patel's%20income%20and%20employment%20with%20documentation%3B%20the%20negotiations%20are%20based%20on%20his%20recollection%20of%20conversations%20during%20each%20hiring%20process.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20college%20senior%20when%20I%20learned%20the%20%26quot%3Bdoor-in-the-face%26quot%3B%20technique%20from%20Robert%20Cialdini's%20book%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftakeaways-from-books-about-human-behavior-published-in-2016-2016-12%23-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInfluence%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20I%20used%20the%20strategy%20when%20I%20started%20applying%20for%20jobs%2C%20and%20it's%20helped%20me%20secure%20higher%20salaries%20in%20each%20job%20negotiation%20throughout%20my%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20software%20engineer%2C%20but%20this%20strategy%20could%20work%20for%20any%20industry.%20You%20only%20need%20data%20on%20typical%20salaries%20for%20a%20specific%20industry%20and%20an%20idea%20of%20the%20specific%20company's%20salary%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22headshot%20of%20a%20man%20in%20a%20white%20and%20navy%20outfit%20in%20front%20of%20a%20door%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ec2af4b8b41a9673fc4f9d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETJ%20Patel.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20TJ%20Patel%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c7069953-0780-4d8a-90b9-6882b8b04af1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20technique%20is%20simple%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDoor%20in%20the%20face%26quot%3B%20is%20when%20someone%20asks%20for%20something%20big%20or%20unreasonable%20in%20an%20initial%20request%20and%20then%20follows%20up%20with%20what%20they%20actually%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20leverage%20%26quot%3Bdoor%20in%20the%20face%26quot%3B%20after%20reading%20Cialdini's%20example%20about%20organizers%20asking%20for%20donations%2C%20where%20they%20start%20by%20asking%20for%20something%20quite%20large%2C%20which%20is%20almost%20certain%20to%20be%20turned%20down%20%E2%80%94%20the%20door%20slamming%20in%20your%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20they%20pivot%20to%20the%20smaller%20%E2%80%94%20and%20truly%20desired%20%E2%80%94%20ask%2C%20which%20suddenly%20seems%20more%20reasonable%20by%20comparison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a104f752-a134-4b02-9519-3f45291119ef%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThat's%20when%20it%20clicked%20for%20me%3A%20I%20could%20use%20this%20same%20principle%20in%20salary%20negotiations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bdoor-in-the-face%26quot%3B%20strategy%20has%20a%20real%20risk%3A%20If%20you%20ask%20for%20too%20much%2C%20an%20employer%20might%20decide%20to%20walk%20away%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20if%20I%20was%20willing%20to%20accept%20that%20possibility%20%E2%80%94%20and%20if%20I%20asked%20respectfully%20and%20backed%20up%20my%20request%20with%20evidence%20like%20competing%20offers%20or%20my%20past%20performance%20%E2%80%94%20then%20most%20reasonable%20employers%20would%20at%20least%20counter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20logic%20was%20that%20if%20they're%20already%20at%20the%20point%20of%20wanting%20to%20hire%20me%2C%20they've%20invested%20time%20and%20resources%20into%20the%20process%2C%20so%20they%20might%20be%20open%20to%20adjusting%20their%20offer%20rather%20than%20starting%20over%20with%20a%20new%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2272fca261-bebd-46d8-af5a-66ea613e4902%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Door%20in%20the%20face'%20has%20been%20crucial%20in%20all%20of%20my%20salary%20negotiations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20reading%20%26quot%3BInfluence%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20every%20job%20offer%20I've%20gotten%2C%20I%20anchored%20the%20negotiation%20on%20a%20number%20much%20higher%20than%20the%20lowest%20I%20was%20willing%20to%20accept.%20Once%20they%20declined%20my%20high%20number%2C%20my%20follow-up%20request%20seemed%20more%20moderate%2C%20and%20employers%20were%20more%20willing%20to%20meet%20me%20in%20the%20middle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20I%20asked%20for%20the%20lower%20amount%20on%20the%20same%20call%3B%20other%20times%2C%20I'd%20wait%20a%20day%20to%20%26quot%3Bthink%20about%20it%26quot%3B%20before%20coming%20back%20with%20a%20more%20%26quot%3Breasonable%26quot%3B%20figure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEither%20way%2C%20the%20technique%20helped%20me%20secure%20offers%20ranging%20from%20%2410%2C000%20to%20%2430%2C000%20more%20in%20total%20compensation%20than%20the%20employers'%20original%20proposal%20%E2%80%94%20and%20more%20than%20I%20expected%20based%20on%20public%20salary%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20the%20offer%20negotiation%20process%20went%20at%20each%20company%20I've%20worked%20at%2C%20including%20t