ltiple%20states%20are%20often%20subject%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bjock%20tax.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20how%20one%20financial%20advisor%20helps%20his%20NFL%20clients%20lower%20their%20tax%20bills%20and%20how%20you%20might%2C%20too.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EHave%20you%20ever%20wondered%20how%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-charitable-remainder-trusts-work-wealth-management-estate-tax-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erich%20and%20famous%3C%2Fa%3E%20do%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Favoid-these-mistakes-tax-filing-irs-audit-trigger-personal-finance-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etaxes%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20maximize%20their%20wealth%20preservation%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJay%20Bass%20has%20a%20behind-the-curtain%20perspective.%20Bass%20is%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20finance%20at%20Rise%20Family%20Office%20and%20managing%20partner%20at%20Rise%20Capital%20Partners%2C%20where%20he%20helps%20professional%20athletes%20with%20tax%20and%20wealth%20planning.%20His%20clients%20include%20Atlanta%20Falcons%20safety%20Jessie%20Bates%20and%20former%20Dallas%20Cowboys%20linebacker%20Jaylon%20Smith.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAthletes%20have%20unique%20financial%20planning%20needs%20due%20to%20the%20nature%20of%20their%20work%2C%20Bass%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Their%20careers%20are%20shorter%2C%20and%20they%20move%20around%20often%20to%20play%20games%20in%20different%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20taxes%2C%20you%20might%20have%20more%20in%20common%20with%20an%20NFL%20athlete%20than%20you%20think%2C%20especially%20if%20you're%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwo-remote-jobs-paying-280k-avoid-burnout-stay-organized-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremote%20worker%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAthletes%20are%20subject%20to%20what's%20known%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bjock%20tax%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20means%20they%20pay%20income%20taxes%20in%20every%20state%20they%20play%20in%2C%20Bass%20said.%20The%20tax%20can%20apply%20to%20salaries%2C%20bonuses%2C%20and%20even%20the%20value%20of%20championship%20rings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tax%20is%20calculated%20by%20the%20number%20of%20days%20a%20worker%20spends%20in%20a%20certain%20state%20as%20a%20proportion%20of%20their%20total%20work%20days%20in%20the%20year.%20The%20tax%20rate%20and%20filing%20requirements%20vary%20from%20state%20to%20state%2C%20and%20some%20states%20don't%20levy%20the%20tax%20at%20all.%20But%20many%20top%20athletes%20could%20be%20looking%20at%20paying%20taxes%20in%2010%20or%20more%20states%20come%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffile-taxes-extension-october-deadline-paperwork-retirement-plans-small-business-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etax%20season%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20jock%20tax%20doesn't%20just%20apply%20to%20pro%20athletes.%20Professionals%20who%20constantly%20cross%20state%20lines%20for%20work%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20coaches%2C%20sports%20officials%2C%20entertainers%2C%20consultants%2C%20and%20remote%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20are%20also%20subject%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20the%20advice%20Bass%20gives%20to%20his%20clients%20could%20apply%20to%20you%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c4a7a4e8-1164-4000-ae99-7e6c0f655d7a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMinimizing%20your%20tax%20bill%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStrategically%20planning%20your%20domicile%26quot%3B%20is%20the%20biggest%20tax%20hack%20Bass%20tells%20his%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20establish%20residency%20in%20states%20that%20have%20favorable%20tax%20structures%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-eliminate-property-taxes-every-state-tax-rate-map-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFlorida%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Texas%2C%20or%20Nevada%2C%20that%20helps%20minimize%20the%20income%20tax%20burden%2C%26quot%3B%20Bass%20said.%20These%20states%20have%20no%20income%20tax%2C%20translating%20to%20significant%20tax%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Bass%20recommends%20planning%20your%20travel%20carefully.%20Athletes%20often%20work%20with%20their%20coaches%20and%20mangers%20to%20plan%20their%20game%20schedules%20to%20spend%20less%20time%20in%20high-tax%20states.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you%20can%20claim%20living%20in%20a%20state%20like%20Florida%20for%20six%20months%20of%20the%20year%2C%20you%20reduce%20the%20amount%20of%20additional%20tax%20incurred%2C%20Bass%20said.%20This%20applies%20to%20remote%20workers%20and%20others%20who%20travel%20frequently%20as%20well%3A%20minimize%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20spent%20in%20high-tax%20states%20to%20the%20best%20of%20your%20ability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMake%20sure%20you%20have%20the%20proper%20documentation%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20a%20driver's%20license%2C%20voter's%20registration%2C%20and%20the%20number%20of%20days%20you%20spend%20in%20and%20out%20of%20state%20%E2%80%94%20to%20clearly%20indicate%20where%20your%20primary%20residence%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20states%20have%20reciprocal%20tax%20agreements%2C%20which%20means%20that%20if%20you%20travel%20between%20those%20states%20for%20work%2C%20you%20won't%20be%20subject%20to%20state%20income%20taxes%20in%20both%20locations.%20Both%20traveling%20workers%20and%20athletes%20can%20take%20advantage%20of%20this%20tax%20situation.%20For%20instance%2C%20Virginia%20and%20Maryland%20have%20a%20reciprocity%20agreement%20that%20reduces%20the%20need%20for%20workers%20to%20file%20taxes%20twice%20between%20the%20two%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20hack%20that's%20used%20by%20top%20athletes%20and%20other%20high-net-worth%20individuals%20is%20donating%20to%20charities%2C%20Bass%20said.%20He's%20helped%20many%20athletes%20and%20entertainers%20set%20up%20charitable%20foundations.%20However%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20a%20high-net-worth%20individual%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20tax%20benefits%20of%20charitable%20contributions.%20Anybody%20can%20make%20a%20donation%20of%20cash%20or%20other%20assets%20to%20an%20IRS-qualified%20501(c)(3)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%2Ftax-deductible-donations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equalified%20charity%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You%20can%20then%20claim%20the%20donation%20as%20an%20itemized%20deduction%20on%20your%20tax%20return%2C%20which%20will%20reduce%20the%20total%20amount%20of%20income%20you%20owe%20taxes%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20many%20professional%20athletes%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20you%20and%20me%2C%20and%20those%20accounts%20are%20another%20way%20they%20reduce%20their%20tax%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaximizing%20your%20tax-advantaged%20accounts%2C%20solo%20401(k)s%2C%20Roth%20IRAs%20%E2%80%94%20those%20are%20some%20of%20the%20things%20we're%20recommending%2C%26quot%3B%20Bass%20said.%20Maxing%20out%20your%20401(k)%20contributions%20reduces%20your%20taxable%20income%2C%20as%20those%20contributions%20are%20made%20with%20pre-tax%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-reduce-income-taxes-high-net-worth-remote-worker-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743583502000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c73cb31aa2ac29ee333cb7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-reduce-income-taxes-high-net-worth-remote-worker-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Athletes%2C%20entertainers%2C%20and%20other%20taxpayers%20who%20travel%20for%20work%20are%20often%20subject%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bjock%20tax%26quot%3B%20for%20every%20state%20they%20earn%20income%20in.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cji%40