as%20assigned%20randomly.%20In%20one%20experiment%2C%20test%20subjects%20were%20given%20either%20a%20lottery%20ticket%20or%20cash.%20Most%20people%20opted%20to%20keep%20whatever%20form%20of%20compensation%20they%20had%20received%20first%20instead%20of%20trading%20it%20for%20the%20other%20option.%20For%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%2C%20whether%20an%20aversion%20to%20feeling%20loss%20or%20a%20bias%20toward%20the%20status%20quo%2C%20people%20tend%20to%20get%20attached%20to%20the%20bird%20in%20their%20hand%2C%20even%20when%20there%20might%20be%20two%20in%20the%20bush.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EList%20prices%20can%20also%20be%20misleading.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-top-markets-housing-outlook-2025-mortgage-rates-miller-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehot%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sellers%20may%20advertise%20their%20homes%20for%20significantly%20less%20than%20what%20buyers%20are%20ready%20to%20pay%20in%20order%20to%20spark%20a%20bidding%20war.%20This%20amounts%20to%20a%20bait-and-switch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20buyer%2C%20don't%20take%20the%20bait.%20Don't%20anchor%20your%20expectations%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-my-zestimate-accurate-home-prices-obsession-zillow-algorithm-homeowner-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elisted%20price%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20anchoring%20effect%20refers%20to%20a%20person's%20tendency%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20first%20piece%20of%20information%20they%20hear%20while%20making%20decisions.%20In%20a%20famous%20lab%20experiment%20by%20the%20late%20Daniel%20Kahneman%20and%20Amos%20Tversky%2C%20research%20subjects%20spun%20a%20wheel%20of%20fortune%20with%20numbers%20from%200%20to%20100.%20The%20participants%20were%20then%20asked%20to%20guess%20the%20share%20of%20African%20countries%20that%20were%20members%20of%20the%20UN.%20Participants%20whose%20spin%20landed%20on%20a%20lower%20number%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20guess%20a%20low%20number.%20Participants%20whose%20wheel%20spin%20landed%20on%20a%20high%20number%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20guess%20a%20high%20number.%20The%20number%20the%20needle%20of%20the%20wheel%20landed%20on%20was%20completely%20irrelevant%2C%20yet%20the%20research%20subjects%20still%20used%20it%20as%20an%20anchor%20for%20their%20guesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20list%20price%20of%20a%20home%20may%20contain%20some%20helpful%20information%20about%20what%20the%20seller%20believes%20its%20value%20is.%20But%20ultimately%20the%20value%20of%20the%20house%20is%20set%20by%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20need%20to%2C%20take%20a%20break.%20Losing%20bidding%20war%20after%20bidding%20war%20%E2%80%94%20which%20happens%20a%20lot%20%E2%80%94%20fosters%20fatigue%20and%20impatience%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20you%20to%20give%20up%20too%20soon%20or%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20you%20later%20regret.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBehavioral%20economists%20have%20repeatedly%20found%20that%20the%20quality%20of%20decisions%20deteriorates%20when%20an%20individual%20is%20overburdened%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonline-shopping-ecommerce-comparison-burnout-too-many-choices-overwhelming-decision-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoo%20many%20options%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20study%20published%20in%20Health%20Economics%20found%20that%20orthopedic%20surgeons%20made%20worse%20recommendations%20toward%20the%20end%20of%20their%20shifts.%20Doctors%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20recommend%20surgery%20for%20patients%20who%20would%20have%20benefited%20just%20as%20much%20from%20surgery%20as%20patients%20seen%20earlier%20in%20the%20surgeon's%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20avoid%20following%20the%20herd.%20If%20others%20are%20ready%20to%20bid%20high%2C%20you%20could%20be%20tempted%20to%20do%20the%20same%20and%20stretch%20your%20budget.%20Herding%20behavior%2C%20another%20behavioral%20economics%20term%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-bubble-home-prices-stay-high-crash-real-estate-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebubbles%20in%20the%20housing%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20the%20stock%20market%20and%20was%20one%20of%20the%20culprits%20for%20the%20subprime%20mortgage%20crisis%20of%202008.%20The%20best%20way%20to%20avoid%20getting%20caught%20up%20in%20speculation%20bubbles%20is%20to%20not%20speculate%20in%20the%20first%20place%20and%20make%20offers%20appropriate%20only%20to%20your%20personal%20financial%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20spending%20a%20few%20weeks%20touring%20homes%20in%20the%20area%2C%20I%20came%20across%20a%20property%20that%20immediately%20caught%20my%20eye.%20It%20had%20everything%20my%20family%20was%20looking%20for.%20But%20there%20was%20one%20giant%20red%20flag%3A%20the%20home%20had%20been%20on%20the%20market%20for%20nearly%20a%20year%20without%20any%20offers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUpon%20further%20inspection%2C%20I%20noticed%20that%20the%20house%20was%20located%20across%20the%20street%20from%20a%20strip%20mall%20and%20had%20a%20strange%20layout.%20Even%20though%20I%20liked%20the%20home%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20avoid%20paying%20more%20than%20other%20buyers%20might%20think%20it%20was%20worth.%20So%20I%20kept%20looking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20buying%20a%20home%2C%20you%20have%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20concern%20yourself%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-home-prices-cities-doge-budget-cuts-elon-musk-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresale%20value%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Life%20is%20unpredictable%3B%20there%20is%20always%20the%20chance%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-orders-accidental-landlords-sell-rent-home-mortgage-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emight%20not%20stay%20in%20the%20home%20long%20term%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20pay%20more%20than%20what%20you%20can%20resell%20it%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20tension%20in%20this%20advice%3A%20a%20homebuyer%20must%20avoid%20herding%20behavior%20by%20thinking%20for%20themself%20while%20simultaneously%20considering%20how%20other%20people%20might%20value%20homes%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20to%20walk%20the%20middle%20path%20is%20detached%20observation%20%E2%80%94%20recognize%20the%20behavior%20patterns%20of%20others%20without%20letting%20it%20unduly%20bias%20your%20decision-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20month%20later%2C%20we%20found%20a%20home%20that%20seemed%20too%20good%20to%20be%20true.%20Ample%20space%2C%20close%20to%20public%20transit%2C%20even%20a%20view%20of%20Puget%20Sound%20and%20the%20Olympic%20Mountains.%20However%2C%20the%20home%20was%2070%20years%20old%2C%20so%20we%20would%20need%20to%20update%20the%20electrical%2C%20plumbing%2C%20and%20heating.%20Since%20we%20were%20renting%20elsewhere%2C%20we%20could%20delay%20moving%20to%20get%20this%20work%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20go%20wrong%20after%20you%20buy%20a%20home.%20Thinking%20that%20these%20problems%20won't%20end%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-renovation-nightmare-home-improvement-contractors-consumer-protection-contract-law-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecosting%20you%20significant%20time%20and%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20what%20behavioral%20economists%20call%20optimism%20bias%3A%20the%20tendency%20to%20overestimate%20the%20likelihood%20of%20favorable%20outcomes%20and%20underestimate%20the%20likelihood%20of%20unfavorable%20outcomes.%20The%20challenge%2C%20then%2C%20is%20to%20consider%20the%20risks%20and%20whether%20they%20are%20worth%20the%20reward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20prepared%20to%20make%20an%20offer%20to%20buy%20a%20home%2C%20I%20thought%20back%20to%20the%20hundreds%20of%20homeowners%20going%20through%20foreclosure%20that%20I%20interviewed%20while%20interning%20at%20the%20Boston%20Fed.%20They%20experienced%20bad%20luck%20on%20top%20of%20bad%20luck%20%E2%80%94%20deaths%2C%20divorces%2C%20medical%20emergencies%2C%20job%20loss%2C%20and%20a%20global%20recession.%20Any%20of%20those%20things%20could%20happen%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20all%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbought-fixer-upper-renovations-million-dollars-family-suffered-marriage-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erepairs%20the%20house%20needed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20determined%20the%20maximum%20amount%20I%20could%20afford%20to%20pay%20was%20%24950%2C000.%20I%20liked%20this%20particular%20home%20more%20than%20any%20other%20home%20on%20the%20market%20priced%20below%20%24950%2C000%2C%20so%20I%20reasoned%20that%20this%20amount%20must%20be%20my%20value%20for%20the%20home.%20But%20I%20still%20had%20a%20nagging%20feeling%20that%20I%20was%20overextending%20myself%20and%20overpaying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20if%20the%20roof%20sprang%20a%20leak%3F%20And%20what%20if%2C%20because%20I%20had%20already%20spent%20my%20savings%20repairing%20the%20plumbing%2C%20electrical%2C%20heating%2C%20and%20cooling%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20any%20money%20left%20to%20repair%20the%20roof%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20have%20kept%20going%20down%20the%20list%20of%20unlikely%20catastrophes.%20Instead%2C%20I%20focused%20on%20the%20unlikeliness%20of%20the%20scenario%20rather%20than%20the%20pain%20of%20the%20scenario.%20This%20helped%20me%20get%20out%20of%20my%20head%20and%20back%20to%20the%20task%20at%20hand.%20In%20economics%2C%20expected%20utility%20theory%20hypothesizes%20that%20individuals%20weigh%20uncertain%20outcomes%20according%20to%20their%20likelihood%20and%20the%20net%20benefit%20of%20each%20outcome.%20I%20shuddered%20at%20the%20thought%20of%20a%20bad%20scenario%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-worried-unemployment-layoffs-recession-jobs-hiring-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20laid%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnext-recession-risk-economic-indicators-grocery-costco-consumer-confidence-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esevere%20recession%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20housing-market%20downturn.%20However%2C%20according%20to%20expected%20utility%20theory%2C%20I%20should%20weigh%20that%20feeling%20against%20the%20likelihood%20of%20that%20scenario%2C%20which%20I%20reasoned%20to%20be%20a%20once-in-a-century%20event.%20In%20all%20likelihood%2C%20my%20job%20was%20safe%2C%20the%20economy%20was%20fine%2C%20and%20the%20value%20of%20homes%20would%20keep%20going%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20home%20was%20listed%20at%20%24840%2C000.%20I%20submitted%20my%20bid%20on%20the%20home%20for%20that%20amount.%20When%20you're%20deciding%20whether%20to%20bid%20above%20or%20below%20the%20asking%20price%2C%20look%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzillow-hottest-housing-markets-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20competitive%20the%20housing%20market%20is%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20neighborhood%20and%20how%20the%20home%20compares%20to%20what%20else%20is%20on%20the%20market.%20If%20the%20market%20is%20cool%2C%20it's%20advisable%20to%20come%20in%20low.%20However%2C%20if%20the%20market%20is%20hot%2C%20the%20seller%20may%20completely%20ignore%20your%20offer%20if%20it's%20below%20the%20asking%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20I%20offered%20%24840%2C000%2C%20I%20was%20ready%20to%20go%20as%20high%20as%20%24940%2C000.%20Later%20that%20day%2C%20my%20agent%20called%20me%20to%20deliver%20the%20good%20news%3A%20we%20won%20the%20home%20at%20list%20price.%20No%20one%20else%20even%20submitted%20a%20bid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fdaryl-fairweather%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDaryl%20Fairweather%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BHate%20the%20Game%3A%20Economic%20Cheat%20Codes%20for%20Life%2C%20Love%2C%20and%20Work%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20chief%20economist%20of%20Redfin.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2