t%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhoever%20said%20history%20repeats%20itself%20was%20not%20talking%20about%20Trump%202.0%20and%20Iran.%20In%202018%2C%20during%20his%20previous%20term%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20unilaterally%20withdrew%20from%20the%20Joint%20Comprehensive%20Plan%20of%20Action%20(JCPOA)%20meant%20to%20restrain%20Iran%20from%20developing%20atomic%20weapons%2C%20calling%20it%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20worst%20possible%20deal%E2%80%9D.%20He%20further%20imposed%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmaximum%20pressure%E2%80%9D%20policy%20that%20led%20to%20an%2081%25%20contraction%20in%20Iran's%20crude%20oil%20exports%2C%20its%20economic%20lifeline.%20He%20authorised%20the%20assassination%20of%20an%20Iranian%20general%20in%20Baghdad%20in%20early%202020.%20Last%20year%2C%20during%20Trump's%20re-election%20campaign%2C%20an%20alleged%20Iranian%20plot%20to%20assassinate%20him%20was%20uncovered.%20On%20February%205%2C%20soon%20after%20re-entering%20the%20White%20House%2C%20Trump%20restored%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmaximum%20pressure%E2%80%9D%20policy%20against%20Iran.%20Subsequently%2C%20the%20US%20intensified%20consultations%20with%20Israeli%20leadership%20to%20prevent%20Iran's%20nuclearisation.%20Why%2C%20then%2C%20exactly%20a%20month%20later%20on%20March%205%2C%20President%20Trump%20wrote%20to%20Iranian%20Supreme%20Leader%20Ayatollah%20Ali%20Khamenei%20proclaiming%20that%20he%20did%20not%20want%20to%20hurt%20Iran%20and%20its%20great%20people%20and%20suggested%20bilateral%20dialogue%20to%20resolve%20the%20nuclear%20issue%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Deception%20Of%20Public%20Opinion'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran's%20reaction%20to%20this%20Trump%20initiative%20was%20equally%20fork-tongued.%20Even%20before%20he%20had%20read%20Trump's%20letter%2C%20the%20Iranian%20Supreme%20Leader%20publicly%20spurned%20the%20offer%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdeception%20of%20public%20opinion%E2%80%9D.%20He%20pointedly%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20know%20they%20won't%20honour%20it%2C%20what's%20the%20point%20of%20negotiating%3F%E2%80%9D%20Three%20weeks%20of%20Iranian%20fire-eating%20rhetoric%20against%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Israel%20followed.%20But%20then%2C%20on%20March%2027%2C%20an%20adviser%20to%20Iran's%20supreme%20leader%20said%20that%20Tehran%20%E2%80%9Chas%20not%20closed%20all%20doors%20to%20resolve%20its%20disputes%20with%20the%20United%20States%20and%20is%20ready%20for%20indirect%20negotiations%20with%20Washington.%E2%80%9D%20Iranian%20Foreign%20Minister%20amplified%2C%20%E2%80%9COur%20policy%20is%20still%20to%20not%20engage%20in%20direct%20negotiations%20while%20under%20%E2%80%98maximum%20pressure'%20and%20military%20threats%2C%20however%2C%20as%20it%20was%20the%20case%20in%20the%20past%2C%20indirect%20negotiations%20can%20continue.%26quot%3B%20Adding%20another%20twist%20to%20the%20tail%2C%20while%20President%20Trump's%20letter%20was%20delivered%20by%20a%20UAE%20official%2C%20an%20Iranian%20response%20was%20conveyed%20via%20Oman%2C%20which%20hosted%20such%20indirect%20US-Iran%20talks%20during%20Biden's%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20exactly%20is%20going%20on%20amidst%20this%20shadowboxing%2C%20and%20what%20is%20the%20likely%20endgame%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Little%20History%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Iran%20was%20never%20colonised%20by%20the%20West%2C%20it%20was%20often%20subject%20to%20political%20coercion%20aimed%20at%20economic%20exploitation%2C%20particularly%20by%20the%20Anglo-Persian%20oil%20company%20founded%20in%201908.%20In%201951%2C%20Iran's%20populist%20Prime%20Minister%20Mohammad%20Mossadegh%20and%20the%20Iranian%20parliament%20nationalised%20the%20company%2C%20prompting%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20US%20to%20covertly%20arrange%20a%20successful%20coup%20against%20the%20elected%20government.%20They%20strengthened%20the%20Shah%2C%20a%20megalomaniac%20autocrat%2C%20who%20acted%20largely%20as%20a%20Western%20vassal%20and%20the%20US-appointed%20%E2%80%9CPoliceman%20of%20the%20Persian%20Gulf%E2%80%9D.%20However%2C%20in%20early%201979%2C%20a%20protracted%20popular%20uprising%20deposed%20him%20and%20brought%20in%20Ayatollah%20Khomeini%2C%20a%20Shia%20clergyman%20and%20fierce%20critic%20of%20Shah%20and%20his%20Western%20backers.%20The%20fledgling%20Islamic%20Republic%20of%20Iran%20(IRI)%2C%20a%20theocratic%20democracy%2C%20was%20born%20and%20tapped%20into%20Iranians'%20adherence%20to%20Shia%20Islam%20and%20anti-Western%20sentiments%20to%20gain%20strength.%20The%20IRI%20survived%20a%20bloody%20eight-year-long%20war%20with%20Iraq%20that%20began%20in%201980%2C%20various%20internal%20dissensions%20and%20insurgencies%2C%20serious%20geo-political%20turbulences%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%2C%20particularly%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%2C%20as%20well%20as%20unmitigated%20Western%20eco-political%20sanctions%20and%20attempts%20to%20isolate%20the%20country%20and%20demonise%20its%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Choking%20Of%20The%20JCPOA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20Tehran's%20nuclear%20technology%20programme%20has%20been%20a%20recurring%20and%20growing%20source%20of%20tensions%20with%20the%20West%20and%20the%20regional%20powers.%20They%20believe%20that%20Iran%2C%20blessed%20with%20huge%20deposits%20of%20hydrocarbons%2C%20does%20not%20need%20an%20extensive%20and%20expensive%20nuclear%20programme.%20It%20is%20widely%20suspected%20to%20be%20a%20Trojan%20Horse%20to%20acquire%20nuclear%20weapon%20capability.%20Although%20Iran%2C%20a%20signatory%20to%20the%20Nuclear%20Non-Proliferation%20Treaty%2C%20has%20always%20denied%20such%20ambitions%2C%20it%20has%20also%20asserted%20its%20right%20to%20nuclear%20technology%20for%20peaceful%20purposes.%20After%20extensive%20negotiations%2C%20seven%20global%20powers%2C%20including%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20Iran%20agreed%20in%202015%20on%20a%20JCPOA%20that%20put%20in%20place%20strict%20restrictions%2C%20including%20an%20International%20Atomic%20Energy%20Agency%20(IAEA)%20inspection%20regime%20on%20the%20Iranian%20nuclear%20programme%2C%20in%20general%2C%20and%20the%20uranium%20enrichment%20cycle%20in%20particular.%20In%20return%2C%20many%20of%20the%20Western%20economic%20sanctions%20on%20Iran%20were%20lifted.%20However%2C%20Trump%201.0's%20withdrawal%20from%20the%20JCPOA%20in%202018%20upended%20the%20arrangement%20and%20provided%20Iran%20with%20the%20justification%20to%20enrich%20uranium%20beyond%20the%20stipulated%2020%25%20limit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20the%20Iranian%20acquisition%20of%20substantive%20missile%20and%20drone%20capabilities%20has%20also%20raised%20eyebrows.%20Its%20robust%20support%20to%20some%20regional%20regimes%20and%20non-state%20actors%2C%20such%20as%20Hamas%2C%20Hezbollah%20and%20Houthis%E2%80%94collectively%20dubbed%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CAxis%20of%20Resistance%E2%80%9D%E2%80%94has%20inflamed%20tensions%20with%20Israel%20and%20the%20US%2C%20which%20last%20month%20jointly%20reiterated%20their%20determination%20to%20disallow%20Iran%20to%20acquire%20a%20nuclear%20weapon%20capability.%20Israel%2C%20widely%20believed%20to%20have%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%20calls%20the%20Iranian%20nuclear%20programme%20%E2%80%9Can%20existential%20threat%E2%80%9D.%20Indeed%2C%20the%20antagonism%20between%20Jewish%20and%20Persian%20civilisations%20dates%20back%20at%20least%20to%20587%20BCE%2C%20when%20the%20first%20Jewish%20temple%20was%20destroyed%20by%20the%20Babylonian%20army%20under%20King%20Nebuchadnezzar%20II.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESuspicion%20Above%20All%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20short%20but%20extensive%20background%20puts%20in%20broad%20relief%20the%20long%20mutual%20suspicion%20arrayed%20against%20any%20successful%20resolution%20of%20Iran-US-Israel%20hostility.%20However%2C%20the%20issue%20is%20as%20broad%20as%20it%20is%20long.%20Iran%20is%20already%20a%20formidably%20potent%20foe%20that%20has%20both%20battle-hardened%2C%20technologically%20competent%20and%20ideologically%20motivated%20military%20capability%20and%20a%20siege%20economy.%20If%20it%20further%20acquires%20deliverable%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%20it%20would%20become%20virtually%20invincible.%20In%20such%20an%20eventuality%2C%20Tehran%20would%20upend%20the%20longstanding%20Pax%20Americana%20in%20the%20Gulf%20and%20could%20configure%20the%20regional%20geostrategic%20stability%20that%20currently%20favours%20US-Israeli%20preponderance.%20Consequently%2C%20both%20Trump%20and%20Netanyahu%20are%20determined%20to%20prevent%20such%20a%20scenario%20from%20coming%20to%20pass.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20any%20objective%20SWOT%20analysis%20would%20show%20that%20Iranian%20nuclear%20assets%20are%20geographically%20diversified%20and%20well-defended%E2%80%94often%20physically%20located%20deep%20underground.%20Tehran%20has%20openly%20warned%20that%20any%20attack%20on%20its%20nuclear%20facilities%20would%20attract%20a%20swift%20and%20disproportionate%20response%20against%20the%20US-Israeli%20interests%20in%20the%20region.%20Further%2C%20such%20an%20act%20is%20likely%20to%20unsettle%20the%20crucial%20global%20oil%20and%20gas%20market.%20While%20the%20Muslim%20Ummah%20is%20not%20quite%20fond%20of%20Iran%20and%20its%20aggressive%20policies%2C%20no%20Muslim%20country%20would%20publicly%20approve%20of%20Iran%20being%20attacked%20in%20this%20manner.%20The%20country's%20regional%20neighbours%2C%20many%20with%20pro-Iran%20Shia%20minorities%2C%20would%20be%20particularly%20wary%20of%20the%20resultant%20instability.%20Although%20the%20clergy-led%20government%20is%20brittle%20and%20unpopular%2C%20a%20foreign%20invasion%20is%20likely%20to%20provide%20a%20much-needed%20rallying%20cry%20for%20its%20support%20base.%20Israel's%20right-wing%20government%20has%20its%20reasons%20for%20not%20only%20supporting%20any%20US%20military%20action%20against%20Iran%20but%20also%20participating%20in%20it%2C%20but%20Iranian%20retaliation%20could%20be%20even%20bigger%20and%20more%20vicious%20than%20seen%20last%20year.%20Moreover%2C%20a%20surgical%20destruction%20of%20nuclear%20capabilities%20would%20not%20be%20enough%2C%20the%20invaders%20may%20need%20to%20ensure%20that%20those%20are%20not%20revived.%20This%20may%20necessitate%20a%20regime%20change%2C%20and%20the%20past%20US%20experiences%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%2C%20viz.%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%2C%20are%20dissuasive.%20Hence%2C%20a%20military%20campaign%20against%20Iran's%20nuclear%20assets%20may%20not%20be%20the%20preferred%20option.%20It%20can%2C%20at%20best%2C%20be%20a%20Pyrrhic%20victory%20without%20any%20guarantee%20of%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20Economy%20Be%20The%20Decider%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran's%20Achilles%20Heel%20is%20its%20economy%2C%20long%20hobbled%20by%20Western%20sanctions%20and%20drained%20by%20the%20heavy%20unproductive%20outgo%20on%20subsidies%2C%20defence%20and%20nuclear%20portfolios%2C%20and%20burdened%20with%20the%20need%20to%20support%20the%20regional%20proxies%20and%20allies.%20While%20Iran%20has%20a%20diversified%20economy%2C%20oil%20and%20gas%20exports%20are%20still%20its%20mainstay.%20The%20Western%20economic%20sanctions%2C%20in%20general%2C%20and%20the%20American%20%E2%80%9Cmaximum%20pressure%E2%80%9D%20campaign%20in%20particular%2C%20have%20seriously%20dented%20it.%20Although%20the%20sanctions%20caused%20serious%20socio-economic%20problems%2C%20such%20as%20public%20disaffection%20due%20to%20high%20inflation%20(40%25%3B%20national%20currency%20has%20lost%2090%25%20of%20its%20value%20since%202018)%2C%20youth%20unemployment%20(22.7%25)%2C%20etc.%2C%20the%20regime%20stayed%20on%20course%20with%20its%20nuclear%20policy.%20During%20the%20past%20few%20months%2C%20however%2C%20the%20regime%20has%20been%20shaken%20as%20its%20regional%20proxies%20(in%20Gaza%2C%20Lebanon%2C%20Syria%20and%20Yemen)%20suffered%20serious%20setbacks.%20Further%2C%20Israeli%20air%20attacks%20and%20covert%20operations%20against%20Iran%20have%20exposed%20the%20latter's%20vulnerabilities.%20The%20regime%20has%2C%20nevertheless%2C%20sought%20to%20exude%20strength.%20It%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20if%20by%20agreeing%20to%20the%20indirect%20negotiations%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20Iran%20is%20indicating%20a%20higher%20degree%20of%20flexibility.%20Tehran's%20counter-offer%20may%20simply%20be%20a%20ploy%20to%20buy%20more%20time.%20For%20Trump%2C%20too%2C%20the%20negotiations%20offer%20a%20low-cost%20option%3A%20an%20agitprop%20strategy%20to%20divide%20the%20Iranian%20leadership.%20Last%20month%2C%20Russia%2C%20too%2C%20offered%20to%20mediate%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Iran%3B%20but%20the%20recent%20turbulence%20in%20the%20Kremlin's%20relations%20with%20the%20White%20House%20over%20the%20Ukrainian%20conflict%20ceasefire%20might%20have%20put%20that%20offer%20in%20some%20doubt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20low%20mutual%20credibility%20and%20long%20list%20of%20grievances%2C%20the%20proposed%20negotiations%20have%20a%20fairly%20small%20chance%20of%20success.%20Similar%20talks%20were%20held%20in%20Oman%20during%20Biden's%20presidency%2C%20and%20they%20failed%20to%20resolve%20the%20issue.%20A%20parallel%20can%20be%20drawn%20with%20three%20well-publicised%20summits%20Trump%20held%20with%20North%20Korean%20leader%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20that%20failed%20to%20denuclearise%20Pyongyang.%20Further%2C%20the%20motives%20of%20the%20two%20sides%20may%20not%20coalesce%3A%20For%20Trump%2C%20a%20successful%20conclusion%20would%2C%20by%20definition%2C%20require%20a%20deal%20tighter%20and%20more%20intrusive%20than%20the%20JCPOA.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Iranian%20leadership%20would%20perhaps%20be%20happy%20to%20buy%20more%20time%2C%20thwart%20the%20threat%20of%20an%20all-out%20war%20and%20negotiate%20a%20reduction%20in%20the%20sanctions%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20Easy%20Deal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20negotiations%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20protracted%20and%20complex.%20In%20case%20a%20breakthrough%20nuclear%20deal%20is%20reached%2C%20the%20possibility%20of%20more%20ambitious%20workover%20straddling%20various%20geopolitical%20and%20economic%20issues%20in%20suspended%20animation%20for%20nearly%20five%20decades%2C%20such%20as%20softening%20of%20Iranian%20anti-US%20and%20anti-Israel%20profile%2C%20faster%20removal%20of%20sanctions%2C%20return%20of%20frozen%20Iranian%20assets%20as%20well%20as%20leveraging%20Iran's%20economic%20opportunities%20for%20hydrocarbons%20and%20infrastructure%2C%20etc.%2C%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out.%20Such%20a%20comprehensive%20US-Iran%20makeover%20would%20have%20profound%20implications%20for%20the%20region%20as%20well%20as%20the%20global%20oil%20and%20gas%20ecosystem.%20Some%20details%20are%20likely%20to%20emerge%20by%20the%20time%20Trump%20pays%20his%20first%20foreign%20visit%20in%20his%20second%20term%20next%20month%20to%20three%20Gulf%20countries%2C%20viz.%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20the%20UAE%20and%20Qatar.%20The%20timeline%20for%20proposed%20indirect%20negotiations%20would%20have%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20the%20lapse%20of%20the%20JCPOA%20architecture%20in%20October%202025%2C%20after%20which%20the%20%E2%80%9CSnapback%E2%80%9D%20of%20some%20other%20sanctions%20on%20Iran%20may%20be%20invoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20different%20level%2C%20it%20would%20be%20fascinating%20to%20watch%20the%20forthcoming%20indirect%20and%20secret%20US-Iranian%20negotiations.%20After%20all%2C%20who%20can%20predict%20the%20outcome%20of%20a%20tryst%20between%20a%20self-styled%20%E2%80%9Ctransactional%E2%80%9D%20deal-maker%20and%20those%20who%20coined%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9CBazaar%E2%80%9D%20and%20raised%20negotiations%20to%20the%20art%20of%20%3Cem%3EMutazayedat%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20or%20overbidding.%20As%20Henry%20Kissinger%20put%20it%20pithily%2C%20albeit%20in%20a%20different%20context%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit's%20a%20pity%20both%20sides%20can't%20lose%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(The%20author%20is%20a%20former%20Indian%20Ambassador%20and%20a%20specialist%20on%20the%20Middle%20East.%20He%20currently%20heads%20Eco-Diplomacy%20and%20Strategies%2C%20a%20Delhi-based%20consultancy.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743581460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2F25geq3f_iran_625x300_02_April_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Ftrump-the-ayatollah-its-a-pity-both-cant-lose-8067975%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Who%20can%20predict%20the%20outcome%20of%20a%20tryst%20between%20a%20self-styled%20%26quot%3Btransactional%26quot%3B%20deal-maker%20and%20those%20who%20coined%20the%20word%20%26quot%3BBazaar%26quot%3B%20and%20raised%20negotiations%20to%20the%20art%20of%20'Mutazayedat'%2C%20or%20overbidding%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Ftrump-the-ayatollah-its-a-pity-both-cant-lose-8067975%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20marketers%20are%20trying%20to%20make%20themselves%20recession-proof%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kraft%20Heinz%20CMO%20on%20stage%20at%20WFA%20Global%20Marketer%20Conference%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ec18d263d72727e198d669%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMoves%20like%20swagger%3A%20Kraft%20Heinz's%20global%20chief%20growth%20officer%2C%20Diana%20Frost%2C%20said%20she%20wants%20her%20marketing%20team%20to%20adopt%20a%20sense%20of%20pride%20and%20swagger%20in%20their%20work.%3Cp%3EWFA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAt%20the%20World%20Federation%20of%20Advertisers%20conference%2C%20it%20was%20clear%20marketers%20are%20under%20pressure.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETariffs%2C%20DEI%20rollbacks%2C%20the%20potential%20for%20ad%20budget%20cuts%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20CMOs%20are%20a%20creative%20bunch.%20They%20told%20me%20they're%20hopeful%20marketing%20can%20steer%20brands%20through.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSnafu%3A%20Situation%20normal%2C%20all%20f%E2%80%94d%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStephan%20Loerke%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20World%20Federation%20of%20Advertisers%2C%20dropped%20this%20f-bomb%20%E2%80%94%20part%20of%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Facronyms-words-radar-taser-snafu-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacronym%20coined%20by%20the%20US%20military%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20Second%20World%20War%20%E2%80%94%20onstage%20at%20the%20ING%20Arena%20at%20the%20trade%20body's%20recent%20flagship%20event%20in%20Brussels.%20He%20said%20it%20was%20an%20apt%20way%20to%20describe%20how%20marketers%20feel%20three%20months%20into%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20marketers%20will%20often%20say%20they're%20at%20their%20most%20creative%20when%20they're%20under%20pressure.%20(Just%20don't%20mention%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-chaos-could-spook-ad-business-spending-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecutting%20their%20budgets%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20duality%20was%20on%20full%20display%20at%20the%20glitzy%20conflab%2C%20replete%20with%20snazzy%20onstage%20graphics%20and%20a%20house%20band%20playing%20electropop%20in%20between%20sessions.%20Speakers%20from%20brands%20like%20Mastercard%2C%20L'Or%C3%A9al%2C%20and%20Kraft%20Heinz%20painted%20an%20optimistic%20vision%20to%20the%202%2C000-strong%20audience%20about%20how%20marketers%20could%20position%20their%20companies%20for%20growth%2C%20despite%20the%20tectonic%20shifts%20happening%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20the%20prospects%20of%20tariffs%2C%20inflation%2C%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20global%20conflicts%2C%20political%20polarization%2C%20and%20the%20disruptive%20impact%20of%20AI%2C%20there's%20a%20lot%20for%20a%20CMO%20to%20keep%20on%20top%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20all%20(99%25)%20of%20the%20roughly%20600%20marketers%20polled%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wfanet.org%2Fknowledge%2Fitem%2F2025%2F03%2F20%2Fwfa-research-identifies-drivers-of-successful-marketing-organisations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20survey%20from%20the%20WFA%20and%20the%20consultancy%20firm%20Oxford%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20economic%20and%20geopolitical%20uncertainty%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20need%20to%20quickly%20adjust%20priorities%20and%20budgets%20%E2%80%94%20would%20be%20important%20or%20more%20important%20in%20the%20next%20five%20years.%20Roughly%20two-thirds%20(68%25)%20said%20they'd%20anticipate%20these%20pressures%20would%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20knock-on%20effect%20of%20that%20is%20ad%20budgets%20are%20likely%20to%20take%20a%20hit.%20Marketing%20is%20often%20the%20first%20department%20to%20feel%20the%20impact%20of%20cost%20cuts.%20In%20separate%20reports%20last%20month%2C%20analysts%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadage.com%2Farticle%2Fagency-news%2Fmadison-and-wall-lowers-2025-us-ad-growth-forecast%2F2605641%3Futm_source%3D%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3D20250318%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMadison%20and%20Wall%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdeadline.com%2F2025%2F03%2Fadvertising-2025-growth-forecast-magna-consumer-confidence-1236351194%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMagna%20Global%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20trimmed%20their%20US%20ad%20market%20forecasts%20for%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22WFA%20CEO%20Stephan%20Loerke%20on%20stage%20in%20Brussels.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ec1c5e69253ccddf9ae5ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221362%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWorld%20Federation%20of%20Advertisers%20CEO%20Stephan%20Loerke%20didn't%20mince%20words.%3Cp%3EWorld%20Federation%20of%20Advertisers%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBackstage%2C%20Loerke%20told%20me%20that%20many%20marketers%20felt%20the%20uncertainty%20was%20at%20an%20inflection%20point%2C%20which%20was%20driving%20conversations%20about%20how%20to%20prove%20marketing's%20value%20as%20CMOs%20prepare%20for%20a%20tough%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUsually%2C%20when%20that%20conversation%20starts%2C%20it%20means%20that%20actually%20there's%20a%20recession%20coming%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Loerke%2C%20a%20former%20marketer%20at%20L'Or%C3%A9al%20in%20the%201990s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20interviewed%20six%20top%20global%20CMOs%20and%20spoke%20with%20other%20marketing%20execs%20attending%20the%20Brussels%20event%20to%20get%20a%20sense%20of%20what's%20top%20of%20mind%20for%20marketers%20as%20they%20navigate%20the%20turbulence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a9317075-286b-4acf-98e7-4b6fa01a3551%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMarketers%20are%20scenario%20planning%20while%20trying%20to%20keep%20on%20track%20with%20their%20long-term%20strategies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20marketers%20are%20spending%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20their%20time%20locked%20in%20scenario-planning%20meetings%20with%20their%20CEOs%2C%20chief%20finance%20officers%2C%20and%20other%20members%20of%20the%20C-suite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBack%20in%20the%20day%2C%20when%20I%20started%20in%20the%20business%2C%20it%20was%20an%20A%20plan%20and%20a%20B%20plan%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Diana%20Frost%2C%20global%20chief%20growth%20officer%20at%20Kraft%20Heinz.%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20that's%20a%20C%20plan%20and%20a%20D%20plan%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20costs%20of%20raw%20materials%20going%20up%2C%20marketers%20in%20sectors%20like%20consumer%20goods%20and%20food%20are%20having%20to%20make%20rapid-fire%20decisions%20about%20prices%2C%20packaging%2C%20and%20product%20formulations.%20Consumers'%20willingness%20to%20pay%20more%20at%20the%20checkout%20is%20often%20partly%20determined%20by%20years%20of%20brand-building%20designed%20to%20make%20them%20choose%20one%20product%20over%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatrik%20Hansson%2C%20EVP%20of%20marketing%20and%20innovation%20at%20the%20dairy%20company%20Arla%20Foods%2C%20said%20that%20while%20companies%20may%20encounter%20a%20year%20with%20disappointing%20growth%2C%20it's%20important%20for%20CMOs%20to%20stick%20to%20their%20plans%20%E2%80%94%20a%20five-year%20horizon%20rather%20than%20a%20six-month%20horizon%2C%20say%20%E2%80%94%20to%20ensure%20their%20marketing%20has%20a%20long-term%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20a%20way%20forward%2C%20then%20a%20bit%20of%20noise%2C%20a%20bit%20of%20turbulence%20doesn't%20distract%20you%20from%20the%20long%20term%2C%20and%20that's%20what%20we're%20trying%20to%20focus%20on%20because%20otherwise%2C%20you%20get%20lost%20in%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Hansson%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216287250-9249-4405-9983-465ab4129084%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20all%20adds%20up%20for%20marketing%20measurement%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20coffees%2C%20canap%C3%A9s%2C%20and%20cocktails%2C%20job%20security%20was%20a%20hot%20topic%20at%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20February%20survey%20published%20Tuesday%20from%20Duke%20University's%20Fuqua%20School%20of%20Business%20found%20that%2063%25%20of%20the%20281%20US%20marketing%20leaders%20polled%20felt%20increased%20pressure%20from%20their%20chief%20finance%20officers%2C%20up%20from%2052%25%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20big%20problems%20is%20that%20the%20advertisers%20themselves%20are%20shedding%20people%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20cut%20costs%2C%20so%20CMOs%20are%20risk-averse%20and%20look%20for%20signs%20of%20success%20that%20are%20supposedly%20measurable%2C%26quot%3B%20Nick%20Manning%2C%20founder%20of%20the%20media%20consultancy%20Encyclomedia%2C%20who%20was%20in%20attendance%2C%20told%20me%20after%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSaying%20'trust%20me%2C%20it'll%20work'%20doesn't%20play%20in%20a%20world%20where%20short-term%20is%20the%20only%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20Manning%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lunch%20at%20WFA%20Global%20Marketer%20Conference%2C%20Brussels%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ec187eb8b41a9673fc4aea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20side%20dish%20of%20marketing%20effectiveness%20chat%20with%20your%20lunch%2C%20sir%3F%3Cp%3EWorld%20Federation%20of%20Advertisers%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDiageo%20is%20often%20seen%20across%20the%20industry%20as%20a%20poster%20child%20for%20demonstrating%20marketing%20effectiveness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20it%20began%20working%20with%20a%20tech%20company%20called%20CreativeX.%20CreativeX%20uses%20artificial%20intelligence%20to%20generate%20a%20%26quot%3Bcreative%20quality%20score%26quot%3B%20that%20predicts%20whether%20digital%20marketing%20assets%20will%20be%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drinks%20giant%20is%20also%20using%20an%20AI%20listening%20tool%2C%20developed%20with%20its%20partners%20Share%20Creative%20and%20Kantar%2C%20to%20predict%20consumer%20trends.%20One%20insight%3A%202025%20is%20the%20year%20of%20%26quot%3Bzebra%20striping%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20consumers%20cut%20down%20on%20their%20alcohol%20consumption%20by%20alternating%20between%20alcoholic%20and%20non-alcoholic%20drinks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiageo's%20marketers%20also%20use%20an%20internal%20tool%20called%20Catalyst%20to%20get%20immediate%20access%20to%20data%20to%20help%20them%20make%20planning%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20our%20marketers%20to%20have%20a%20business%20mindset%20and%20delve%20into%20the%20insights%20we%20can%20now%20access%20to%20plan%20spend%2C%20design%20campaigns%2C%20create%20content%2C%20and%20collaborate%20with%20partners%20based%20on%20what%20scenario%20best%20delivers%20the%20brand-building%20outcome%20that%20drives%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cristina%20Diezhandino%2C%20Diageo's%20chief%20marketing%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Kraft%20Heinz%2C%20Frost%20wants%20to%20instill%20a%20sense%20of%20swagger%20and%20pride%20within%20the%20marketing%20department%20%E2%80%94%20and%20she's%20got%20the%20receipts%20to%20back%20it%20up.%20The%20Heinz%20brand%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20has%20marked%20compound%20annual%20revenue%20growth%20of%206%25%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20adding%20around%20%24600%20million%20in%20top-line%20growth%20to%20the%20broader%20Kraft%20Heinz%20business%2C%20Frost%20said.%20She%20credits%20the%20creation%20of%20its%20internal%20digital%20ad%20agency%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Kitchen%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20also%20the%20repeatable%20frameworks%20it's%20put%20in%20place%20for%20Heinz%20marketers%20around%20the%20world%20to%20help%20grow%20the%20brand%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20have%20these%20proof%20points%20of%20growth%2C%20then%20you%20can%20build%20the%20pride%2C%20then%20you%20can%20build%20the%20momentum%20of%20how%20it's%20actually%20possible%20as%20you%20roll%20it%20out%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20portfolio%2C%20%26quot%3B%20Frost%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220b250ba0-de64-4107-bace-fa38902ce2a3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EJitters%20over%20brand%20safety%20and%20DEI%20rollbacks%20loomed%20large%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBrand%20safety%26quot%3B%20was%20the%20elephant%20in%20the%20room%20at%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnspoken%20but%20present%20were%20lawsuits%20filed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-x-adds-more-advertisers-to-antitrust-lawsuit-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk's%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadvertisers-hit-back-at-rumble-boycott-antitrust-lawsuit-filing-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evideo%20platform%20Rumble%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20plus%20a%20Jim%20Jordan-led%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-judiciary-committee-probe-garm-brand-safety-conservative-media-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHouse%20Judiciary%20Committee%20investigation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20took%20aim%20at%20the%20WFA's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fad-group-to-suspend-garm-initiative-following-elon-musk-lawsuit-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enow-shuttered%3C%2Fa%3E%20voluntary%20initiative%2C%20the%20Global%20Alliance%20of%20Responsible%20Media%2C%20and%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20of%20its%20advertiser%20members.%20The%20lawsuits%20and%20the%20probe%2C%20which%20are%20ongoing%2C%20allege%20GARM's%20members%20illegally%20colluded%20to%20boycott%20platforms%20like%20X%20and%20Rumble.%20While%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fad-group-to-suspend-garm-initiative-following-elon-musk-lawsuit-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGARM%20closed%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20the%20WFA%20said%20was%20due%20to%20its%20limited%20resources%2C%20the%20WFA%20has%20said%20it%20adhered%20to%20competition%20rules%20and%20would%20prove%20so%20in%20court.%20The%20WFA%20told%20me%20in%20Brussels%20it%20didn't%20want%20to%20discuss%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(Side%20note%3A%20For%20all%20its%20glamour%2C%20the%20WFA's%20event%20had%20been%20originally%20due%20to%20take%20place%20at%20the%20far-flung%20locale%20of%20Mumbai%2C%20India%2C%20but%20after%20the%20legal%20troubles%20arose%2C%20it%20was%20shifted%20to%20Brussels%2C%20where%20the%20WFA%20is%20headquartered.%20The%20WFA%20partnered%20with%20the%20local%20advertising%20trade%20body%2C%20the%20UBA%2C%20to%20run%20the%20main%20show.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22WFA%20Global%20Marketer%20Week%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ec1f8163d72727e198d814%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20bull%20market%20for%20marketing%3A%20Attendees%20packed%20the%20former%20Brussels%20stock%20exchange%20building%20to%20dine%20and%20dance%20at%20the%20gala%20dinner.%3Cp%3EWorld%20Federation%20of%20Advertisers%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20GARM%20was%20off%20limits%2C%20marketers%20did%20open%20up%20about%20another%20topic%20that's%20become%20newly%20contentious%2C%20particularly%20in%20corporate%20America%3A%20the%20anti-woke%20movement%20and%20the%20vocal%20backlash%20against%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20inclusion%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGael%20de%20Talhouet%2C%20VP%20of%20brand%20building%20at%20the%20Swedish%20hygiene%20company%20Essity%2C%20said%20marketers%20should%20be%20mindful%20that%20%26quot%3Ba%20brand%20is%20not%20a%20political%20stage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20where%20you%20tell%20people%20about%20the%20good%20you%20bring%20to%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERupen%20Desai%2C%20CMO%20and%20venture%20partner%20of%20the%20Una%20Terra%20Early%20Growth%20Fund%2C%20said%20the%20recent%20DEI%20rollbacks%20had%20revealed%20two%20types%20of%20companies%3A%20those%20where%20DEI%20was%20hard-coded%20into%20the%20company's%20economic%20model%20and%20those%20that%20were%20investing%20in%20these%20sorts%20of%20programs%20just%20because%20everyone%20else%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20second%20type%20of%20company%2C%20Desai%20said%20the%20recent%20movements%20are%20a%20%26quot%3Bhuge%20sigh%20of%20relief.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20grappling%20with%20growth%2C%20or%20the%20lack%20of%20it%2C%20and%20this%20investment%20isn't%20really%20yet%20showing%20results%2C%20it's%20probably%20easier%20to%20take%20a%20step%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20Desai%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20companies%20who%20continue%20on%20this%20journey%20will%20be%20bigger%20winners%20than%20the%20ones%20who%20took%20a%20step%20forward%2C%20took%20a%20step%20back.%2