t%2C%20software%20engineering%20applicants%20would%20sometimes%20deputize%20a%20friend%20to%20spit%20out%20code%20in%20their%20place%20(either%20in%20a%20take-home%20test%20or%2C%20as%20one%20recruiter%20told%20me%2C%20actually%20sending%20someone%20else%20in%20their%20place%20to%20the%20interview%20round)%2C%20and%20job%20seekers%20would%20share%20coding%20tests%20and%20answers%20online.%20If%20you%20search%20Reddit%2C%20TikTok%2C%20or%20Blind%2C%20you'll%20find%20people%20sharing%20tips%20and%20tricks%20to%20con%20an%20interviewer.%20But%20AI%20is%20a%20knowledgeable%20friend%20who's%20even%20easier%20to%20access.%20More%20people%20are%20using%20it%20to%20try%20to%20land%20any%20job%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-applications-hiring-ai-bots-spam-resume-cover-letter-2024-3%3Futm_source%3Dfacebook%26utm_medium%3Dsocial%26utm_campaign%3Dbusiness-art-headline-post-comment%26fbclid%3DIwY2xjawJYxkJleHRuA2FlbQIxMAABHcoBQjC_kuq-4sJBVaTpgtEwrO7v-dpNeyTaxZggabxhvjva3Mb4JhHBdA_aem_SX7YahFxRST-bu3LTwj9zg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emass%20applying%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20sending%20AI-generated%20cover%20letters.%20Overwhelmed%20recruiters%20then%20use%20their%20own%20AI%20tools%20to%20try%20to%20sift%20through%20and%20find%20the%20best%20candidates.%20It's%20all%20creating%20a%20massive%20cog%2C%20with%20two%20different%20AIs%20talking%20to%20each%20other%20and%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-broken-linkedin-ai-fix-fewer-jobs-resume-spammers-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ejob%20seekers%20and%20hiring%20managers%20feeling%20frustrated%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%20engineers%2C%20recruiters%20and%20hiring%20managers%20started%20to%20notice%20something%20was%20amiss%20by%20early%202023.%20Job%20applicants%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-interviewers-cant-tell-job-candidates-use-chatgpt-cheat-coding-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecompleted%20coding%20tests%20with%20perfect%20answers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20when%20they%20moved%20on%20to%20interviews%20about%20the%20test%2C%20some%20knew%20little%20to%20nothing%20about%20the%20work%20they'd%20submitted.%20%26quot%3BEven%20with%20ChatGPT%20earlier%20versions%2C%20it%20could%20solve%20a%20lot%20of%20coding%20questions%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Yang%20Mou%2C%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20AI%20recruiting%20company%20Fonzi.%20%26quot%3BThe%20thing%20that's%20even%20more%20insidious%20now%20is%20that%20the%20AI%20is%20also%20better%20at%20explaining%20the%20answers%20as%20if%20it%20was%20a%20human.%26quot%3B%20Fonzi%20interviewed%201%2C270%20candidates%20for%20a%20software%20engineering%20job%20between%20January%20and%20March%2C%20and%20flagged%2023%25%20of%20them%20%26quot%3Bas%20likely%20to%20be%20using%20external%20tools%2C%26quot%3B%20Mou%20says.%20The%20AI%20tool%20scans%20answers%20for%20awkwardly%20long%20pauses%20and%20evaluates%20phrases%20used%20to%20see%20the%20likelihood%20that%20they've%20been%20written%20by%20a%20chatbot%2C%20and%20then%20humans%20can%20listen%20back%20to%20the%20interview%20to%20see%20if%20they%20catch%20any%20red%20flags.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20technical%20interview%20company%20Karat%20flagged%20about%202%25%20of%20interviewees%20as%20potential%20cheaters.%20Now%2C%20that%20proportion%20has%20jumped%20to%2010%25%20of%20interviewees.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20happening%20more%20frequently%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jeffrey%20Spector%2C%20the%20cofounder%20and%20president%20of%20Karat.%20%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20our%20belief%20is%20that%20interviews%20have%20to%20evolve.%26quot%3B%20Karat%20is%20developing%20a%20new%20interview%20process%20that%20it%20hopes%20will%20better%20evaluate%20job%20seekers%20when%20they%20use%20LLMs%2C%20Spector%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BThe%20LLM%20is%20becoming%20a%20core%20part%20of%20how%20engineers%20do%20their%20job.%20Preventing%20them%20from%20using%20the%20tools%20on%20their%20job%20seems%20very%20unnatural.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20AI%20becomes%20a%20bigger%20part%20of%20the%20job%2C%20Spector%20says%2C%20hiring%20managers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20humanity%20at%20large%20%E2%80%94%20have%20to%20ask%20the%20question%3A%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20you%20define%20cheating%3F%26quot%3B%20He%20says%20people%20shouldn't%20disregard%20explicit%20instructions%20not%20to%20use%20AI%2C%20but%20if%20most%20people%20are%20using%20it%20and%20you're%20not%2C%20you%20might%20be%20at%20a%20disadvantage%20in%20the%20interview%20process.%20Many%20applicants%20use%20books%20and%20online%20tips%20to%20study%20for%20coding%20interviews%2C%20and%20some%20use%20ChatGPT%20to%20practice%20for%20job%20interviews.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20using%20AI%20in%20the%20actual%20test%2C%20Spector%20says%2C%20a%20tipping%20point%20will%20come%20where%20it%20feels%20too%20disadvantageous%20not%20to%2C%20particularly%20among%20young%20engineers%20who%20have%20learned%20and%20grown%20up%20in%20the%20LLM%20era%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20ethical%20questions%20will%20get%20messier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHadi%20Chami%2C%20the%20director%20of%20solution%20engineering%20at%20the%20software%20company%20Apryse%2C%20says%20he%20began%20to%20notice%20ways%20job%20candidates%20were%20using%20LLMs%20as%20he%20started%20to%20use%20them%20more%20in%20his%20own%20work.%20So%20he%20changed%20the%20job%20application%20last%20year.%20Now%2C%20he%20gives%20applicants%20who%20pass%20a%20first%20%26quot%3Bvibe%20check%26quot%3B%20interview%20a%20take-home%20assignment%2C%20with%20the%20expectation%20they'll%20use%20AI.%20But%20he%20tells%20them%20they'll%20have%20to%20walk%20him%20through%20their%20work.%20That's%20helpful%20for%20now%2C%20as%20he%20can%20still%20see%20whether%20they%20know%20why%20something%20works%2C%20not%20just%20that%20it%20does%20work.%20But%20Chaim%20expects%20the%20problem%20to%20get%20worse%3A%20He%20says%20that%20he's%20concerned%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-damage-gen-z-careers-tech-layoffs-job-market-hiring-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eyoung%20workers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20coming%20into%20the%20field.%20%26quot%3BThey%20may%20have%20an%20overreliance%20on%20the%20tool.%20They'll%20be%20able%20to%20ace%20all%20their%20classes%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20might%20struggle%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20this%20isn't%20the%20interview%20apocalypse%20scenario%20it%20seems.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20little%20of%20a%20new%20frontier%2C%20which%20is%20maybe%20why%20there%20is%20so%20much%20fear%20and%20stress%20on%20both%20sides%20and%20people%20are%20just%20flailing%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Victoria%20Gates%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20the%20interview%20training%20firm%20Expert%20Interviews.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20investing%20your%20time%20and%20your%20money%20into%20finding%20out%20if%20candidates%20are%20cheating%2C%20you're%20wasting%20your%20time.%20The%20way%20interview%20processes%20are%20today%2C%20they%20are%20very%20unfair%20towards%20candidates.%20Of%20course%20they're%20going%20to%20try%20to%20find%20anything%20they%20can.%26quot%3B%20Instead%20of%20trying%20to%20go%20full%20bad%20cop%20and%20employ%20tech%20to%20monitor%20cheating%2C%20Gates%20says%20companies%20should%20train%20interviewers%20to%20ask%20incisive%20follow-up%20questions%20and%20for%20specific%20examples%20that%20LLMs%20can't%20generate.%20Right%20now%2C%20companies%20may%20be%20focused%20on%20catching%20cheaters%2C%20but%20Ali%20Ansari%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20AI%20interview%20company%20Micro1%2C%20says%20that%20will%20change.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20coding%20in%20general%20is%20already%20looking%20extremely%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat%20implies%20even%20without%20the%20cheating%2C%20the%20coding%20test%20will%20have%20to%20start%20looking%20different.%26quot%3B%20He%20predicts%20that%20there%20will%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bnew%20norm%26quot%3B%20for%20coding%20interviews%20within%20the%20next%20year%20or%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20coding%20mess%20is%20evidence%20of%20the%20breakdown%20in%20trust%20between%20employers%20and%20workers.%20Job%20seekers%20are%20questioning%20how%20much%20free%20labor%20they%20owe%20someone%20who%20may%20not%20even%20extend%20them%20a%20second%20interview%2C%20and%20more%20bosses%20are%20doubting%20the%20integrity%20and%20work%20ethic%20of%20the%20people%20reporting%20to%20them.%20So%20much%20of%20the%20tech%20meant%20to%20make%20job%20searching%20easier%20and%20more%20accessible%20has%20just%20added%20noise%20to%20the%20process.%20Killing%20the%20old%20coding%20test%20and%20using%20something%20more%20creative%20in%20its%20place%20may%20be%20a%20small%20step%20in%20repairing%20that%20disconnect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheating-tech-interviews-soaring-managers-lost-gen-ai-chatgpt-coding-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743581341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ec53db63d72727e198e5f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheating-tech-interviews-soaring-managers-lost-gen-ai-chatgpt-coding-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20'perfect%20storm'%20has%20made%20coding%20interviews%20a%20cheater's%20paradise%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ahoover%40insider.com%20(Amanda%20Hoover)